Estrogens play a multifaceted role in the central nervous system (CNS), influencing synaptic plasticity, neuronal development, and survival in newly formed spinal synapses, as well as promoting neural stem cell proliferation and maintaining the integrity of the blood-brain barrier (
McCullough et al., 2003
;
Mukai et al., 2010
;
Frick et al., 2015
;
Na et al., 2015
). Both neuron- and astrocyte-derived estrogens are believed to contribute significantly to neuroprotection and cognitive function through interactions with ERs expressed in multiple brain regions (
McEwen and Woolley, 1994
;
McEwen et al., 1995
;
Azcoitia et al., 2001
).

