4 Role of estrogens in neuronal function
Preclinical and human studies have shown that ERα is abundantly expressed in the hypothalamus, particularly in the preoptic area (POA), ventromedial nuclei (VMN), amygdala, and periventricular nuclei (PV). ERβ exhibits a similar distribution, maintaining high expression in the POA, bed nucleus of the stria terminalis (BNST), PV, and supraoptic nuclei (
Laflamme et al., 1998
;
Azcoitia et al., 2001
;
Kruijver et al., 2003
;
Mitra et al., 2003
;
Kelly and Ronnekleiv, 2012
). ERβ is also expressed in the hippocampus, amygdala, and cerebral cortex, where it participates in adult neurogenesis, synaptic plasticity, and new neuron formation (
Weiser et al., 2008
).

